article.description: Adkins leads Northwestern St past Nicholls 48-21
article.headline: Adkins leads Northwestern St past Nicholls 48-21
article.linkText: Adkins leads Northwestern St past Nicholls 48-21
article.story: NATCHITOCHES, La. -- Zach Adkins threw for 180 yards with five touchdowns and ran for a sixth as Northwestern State rolled past Nicholls 48-21 on Saturday night. Garrett Atzenweiler pushed Northwestern State (6-5, 4-3 Southland) ahead with a 1-yard touchdown run and Adkins threw scoring strikes of 17 yards to Zach White and 24 yards to Cody Jones for a 28-7 halftime lead. Adkins connected with Jones and Tuff McClain in the third quarter, and scored on a 3-yard keeper with 9:31 remaining. Adkins went 17 of 20 -- completing his first nine attempts -- without an interception. Jones had four receptions for 68 yards. Daniel Taylor finished with 80 of the Demons' 300 rushing yards. Michael Henry paced Nicholls (0-11, 0-7) with 146 yards on 29 carries, including a 19-yard touchdown on the games' opening drive. Beaux Hebert hit Demon Bolt for a 2-yard score to make it 35-14 in the third.
